<Note>
<Para>A VFSG system is considered to be operating normally if its associated status message (ELEC GEN SYS L1, L2, R1 or R2) is not displayed.  </Para>
</Note>
<Para>Deactivate the inoperative cabin air compressor and confirm that associated check valve operates normally (AMM DDG 21-51-01).</Para>
<List listType="1.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Set the affected cabin air compressor power switch OFF on the MISC SYSTEM CTRLS (MSC) maintenance page.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Confirm associated cabin air compressor check valve operates normally:</Para>
<List listType="A.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Set associated air conditioning pack ON for five minutes.</Para>
<Note>
<Para>If the RAF is inoperative, the pack will not operate on the ground. The PACK L or PACK MODE L advisory message will be displayed when ram air duct cooling is not available.</Para>
</Note>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>On AIR CONDITIONING maintenance page 1, confirm that COMP OUT temperature of the inoperative CAC is at least 10 degrees C less than the COMP OUT temperature of the associated operating CAC.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>For check valve not operating normally, set associated pack OFF.  The airplane may be dispatched using MEL item 21-52-01.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</MaintenanceProcedure>
<OperationNote>
<List listType="1.">
<ListItem>
<Para>If cabin temperatures become warmer than desired, consider one or more of the following temporary actions:</Para>
<List listType="A.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Select IFE system modes designed to reduce cabin heat loads.</Para>
<Note>
<Para>Availability of modes dependent on IFE system installed and airline modifiable options.</Para>
</Note>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Set IFE off using the IFE Power switch on the Video Control Station.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Select HEAT REDUCTION mode using the Cabin Attendant Panel TEMPERATURE menu (adjusts cabin lighting and window shading).</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Effectivities>
<Effectivity>For FCAC installed:</Effectivity>
</Effectivities>
<Para>If on ground, set FCAC OFF.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>If cabin or flight deck temperatures become too cool, climbing to a higher altitude will increase the heating capability of the air conditioning system.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>In the cruise mode, the cabin altitude is normally at or below 6,000 feet.  During some degraded operations, the cabin altitude may increase to 8,000 feet.  This can occur if the air conditioning system is not achieving cabin temperature and ventilation rate targets, and would be more likely with an inoperative pack or CAC.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>For only L1 CAC inoperative, PACK R Advisory message may be displayed for approximately 60 seconds after takeoff and after landing.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>For only R1 CAC inoperative, PACK L Advisory message may be displayed for approximately 60 seconds after takeoff and after landing.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</OperationNote>
</DispatchProcedure>
